eigenfunctions of the harmonic oscillator,
or any other potential for this matter.

94
00:06:28,226 --> 00:06:32,510
So these coefficients determine the
probability of us finding the particle,

95
00:06:32,510 --> 00:06:35,570
in the single particle case, or
the density of particles, let's say,

96
00:06:35,570 --> 00:06:39,910
in the many particle case,
in a specific new eigenstate.

97
00:06:39,910 --> 00:06:46,233
So Cn squared is exactly
the probability of

98
00:06:46,233 --> 00:06:51,502
finding our particle in the state,

99
00:06:51,502 --> 00:06:56,946
psi sub n (2), which again refers

100
00:06:56,946 --> 00:07:02,215
to the potential after the quench,

